  "detailed_description": "Hag\u2019s Castle is a 3D Action Adventure game, inspired by classics like \u2018Dungeon Master\u2019 and \u2018Eye Of The Beholder\u2019.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe game features real-time combat with a range of crusty creatures that have usurped the hallowed opulence of an ancient Scottish Castle. You, playing as a \u2018Wizard\u2019s lackey\u2019, have been asked to perform the quest of rescuing the wizard\u2019s pet dragon \u2018Oli\u2019 from the clutches of an evil old witch named \u2018Madam Hag\u2019. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThere are twenty-five levels in the game, and the player can control movement, fighting and spell-casting entirely with mouse control.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIt\u2019s also the first game from Ed Sludden, a veteran Games Artist from the UK with experience working on titles such as \u2018Conker\u2019s Bad Fur Day\u2019, \u2018Bonsai Barber\u2019 and \u2018Adventure Time - Pirates of the Enchiridion\u2019.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe music in \u2018Hag\u2019s Castle\u2019 is by Graeme Norgate,  a Bafta nominated composer who has worked on video game soundtracks since the late 80\u2019s. Graeme wrote the music on games such as Killer Instinct, Blast Corps, Goldeneye and Perfect Dark.",
